# Visual & Code Standard Rules

- **CRITICAL**: When adding new Lucide icons, UI components, or utilities, ALWAYS verify that the necessary imports are added to the top of the file to prevent ReferenceErrors at runtime.
- **CRITICAL (Encoding)**: ALWAYS ensure all files are saved in **UTF-8** encoding. Thai characters must remain readable and not corrupted by system-default encodings (like CP874).
- **CRITICAL (Mojibake Prevention)**: NEVER copy Thai text from terminals, diffs, logs, or shells if it appears garbled (e.g. `เธ`, `เน€`). When shell output is mojibake, retype the Thai text from a UTF-8-safe editor/source or use explicit Unicode escapes (`\u0e..`) for labels/strings. After editing files that contain Thai text, verify the saved source or rendered UI still displays proper Thai before finishing.
- Maintain Thai language support in all UI and file content (UTF-8).
- Prioritize high-end aesthetics (Glassmorphism, gradients, modern typography).
- Verify design consistency across different screen sizes before completion.
- When navigating from a lesson page back to its course detail page, use `navigate(courseDetailPath, { replace: true })` so the browser Back action returns to the course list instead of reopening the lesson.
- The top back button on course detail pages must always navigate statically to `/user/courses`, never use `navigate(-1)` or browser history.
- When the route changes, reset the active scroll container and `window` back to top so each new page starts at the top of the content.
- **Large Desktop Layout**: Maintain a responsive sidebar (`md:260px / xl:280px / 2xl:300px`) and use wider containers (`max-w-[1450px]` - `1600px`) for ultra-wide displays.
- **Container Gutters**: Ensure all main content sections have internal padding (e.g., `xl:px-10 2xl:px-12`) so content never "sticks" to the edges of its max-width container on high-resolution monitors.
- **Document Viewer**: Simplify the desktop UI by hiding the bottom footer bar; integrate the "Mark as Complete" logic into the top close button so closing the viewer automatically saves progress.
- **Mobile Equal Height Cards**: When creating a horizontal scroll container on mobile, ALWAYS use CSS Grid (`grid grid-flow-col auto-cols-[...] items-stretch`) instead of Flexbox to ensure all cards maintain a perfectly equal height regardless of content length. Use a `div` wrapper around interactive elements like `button` inside the grid cells to ensure the browser stretches them correctly.
- **Admin Permissions**: Separate system management (Superadmin) from content management (Sub-admin/Manager). Use `verifySuperAdmin` middleware for sensitive operations (Users, Tiers, Departments, Settings, Rewards) and allow Managers to manage Courses, Lessons, and Reports by using `verifyAdminPanelAccess`.
- **Portal First (Modals & Overlays)**: ALWAYS use `ModalPortal` (using `createPortal()`) when creating or modifying Modals, Popovers, Action Menus, Dropdowns, or Tooltips. Never render `position: fixed` overlays inline inside normal component trees. This ensures they mount to `document.body`, escaping CSS "Containing Block" traps caused by ancestor `transform`, `filter`, `backdrop-filter`, or `overflow: hidden` properties, guaranteeing true full-viewport positioning and preventing layout clipping (e.g., White screen or confined backdrop bugs). Every modal MUST implement `backdrop-blur-md` and `bg-slate-950/65` (or `bg-black/40` for system dialogs) and handle scroll locking via the Portal.

- **CourseCard Design Standard**:
    - **Container**: Use `rounded-[1.8rem]`, `border-slate-200/80`, and a soft premium shadow (`0 22px 45px -36px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.24)`).
    - **Media Section**: Maintain an `aspect-[16/10]` ratio with a bottom-to-top gradient overlay (`from-slate-950/72`).
    - **Meta Row**: Display `lessonCount` and `durationLabel` with corresponding Lucide icons at the top of the content area.
    - **Centered Badge**: When `isTemporary` is true, the expiration badge MUST be centered using `flex justify-center`.
    - **Footer Area (`border-t`)**:
        - **Left Side**: Always place the **Progress Bar** and **Percentage** here (left-aligned).
        - **Right Side**: Always place **Points** and **"แต้มรวม"** label here (right-aligned).

- **Standard Clean Code & Architecture Rules (v1.8.3)**:
    - **No Blocking UI**: NEVER use `window.alert()` or `window.confirm()`. Use `useToast()` for notifications and `useConfirm()` for destructive actions.
    - **Auth & Permissions**: All backend services MUST use `authHelpers.getActorContext(prisma, authUser)` for actor resolution and `authHelpers.buildVisibilityWhere` for Prisma filtering. Never implement duplicate role-checking logic in local services.
    - **Visibility Scoping**: When fetching Courses or Categories, always apply the scoping logic from `auth.helpers.js` to ensure users only see content allowed for their Department or Tier.
    - **Component Sustainability**: Keep files under 400 lines. If a component grows larger, extract logic into a dedicated custom hook or sub-component.
    - **Localization**: No hardcoded Thai strings in UI code. Add all labels to `src/locales/th.json` and use the `t()` translation hook.
    - **Date Standardization**: Static date formatting must use `dateUtils.js`. Thai year conversion must use the `toThaiYear` helper.
    - **Database Security**: Never hardcode credentials. Use `.env` variables and ensure `DATABASE_URL` (pooler) and `DIRECT_URL` (direct) are correctly mapped in production (Vercel).
